comment:
It would be helpful if roles and permissions could be more granular.

 For example, teachers require the permission 'Student Profile: Action: Meals: Administer My Students' in order to {color:#14892c}take the meals register{color} each morning but this also gives the following {color:#d04437}other permissions{color} that give (in my view) far more access to the system that teachers should routinely have:

 {color:red}- View/add/modify/delete dietary requirements for students assigned to the user.{color}

 {color:red}- Create/setup/delete meals.{color}

 {color:red}- Create and change provisions (but NOT meal provision prices) for students assigned to the user.{color}

 {color:red}- Managing meal sittings and add automatic attendees among students assigned to the user.{color}

 {color:red}- Create and change meal patterns for students assigned to the user.{color}

 {color:#14892c}- Add and change meal choices for students assigned to the user.{color}

 {color:red}- View/add/change meal sessions, add staff and students assigned to the user to meal sessions, open registers.

 - View meal reports{color}

 {color:#333333}There is a similar issue for Administering My Students Attendance. Also the ability to administer staff profile pictures is built in to a level of access to HR information that administrative colleagues would not normally have{color}

 This granularity could be achieved either by further separating permissions (but understand that this could get ridiculous) or by the ability to tick and cross specific permissions when granting the over-arching permission.
